.\" Man page for ocode acp
.TH OCODE-ACP 1 "June 2025" "ocode" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ocode-acp \- Run ACP (Agent Communication Protocol) server over stdio
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ocode acp
[\fIoptions\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Run the Agent Communication Protocol (ACP) server over standard input/output.
This allows other programs to communicate with ocode via JSON messages.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Show this help message and exit.
.SH PROTOCOL
The ACP server communicates via JSON messages over stdin/stdout.
It expects messages of type "message" with "content" and optional "sessionId" fields.

.TP
Input message format:
.B {"type": "message", "content": "Hello", "sessionId": "abc123"}
.TP
Output message format:
.B {"type": "text", "content": "Response...", "sessionId": "abc123"}
.TP
Error format:
.B {"type": "error", "message": "Error description"}
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Start ACP server:
.B ocode acp
.TP
Send a message (from another process):
.B echo '{"type": "message", "content": "Hello"}' | ocode acp
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ocode (1),
.BR ocode-run (1)